sentences: Hotz was engineer and did programming on B.B. King's Grammy-nominated King of the Blues: 1989.
Hotz was also the engineer on King's Grammy-nominated "Standing on the Edge of Love", for Best Contemporary Blues Recording in 1988 (from The Color of Money soundtrack).
In 2011 he released his debut novel, The Gates of Time.
"Zuma" won a 2001 Innovation award from Computer Graphics World Magazine and was used on the 2001 NSYNC PopOdyssey tour.
